{"questionId":"12095","questionHtml":"<p>Use the trapezoidal rule to find an estimate for the area.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Area&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{1.1}}{2}\\left( {2 + 2\\left( {5 + 15 + 47} \\right) + 148} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>15</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>47</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>148</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Area = 156 units<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12095","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.7a.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use the trapezoidal rule to find an estimate for the area.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.8—Trapezoid rule","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}